============================================================
CONCLUSION:
Transfer matrix g_k has degree k (natural combinatorial meaning).
Opus g_k has degree 3 for k>=3 (valid reparametrization).
Both give the same CV^2. Neither is 'wrong'.
The degree-3 universality is a property of the DECOMPOSITION,
not of the individual matching weights.

============================================================
WHY DEGREE-3 REPARAMETRIZATION EXISTS:
The transfer matrix M(x) is 3x3. Its characteristic polynomial
p(lambda) = lambda^3 - lambda^2 - x*lambda - x constrains
lambda_1(x) = 1 + 2x + O(x^2). The 3 eigenvalues generate
at most 3 exponential terms in M^N, which gives at most
3 independent functions of N (hence m). Any higher-degree
polynomial in m can be re-expressed using these 3 functions,
hence the degree-3 reparametrization exists.
This is fundamentally because the Z_j process has TRIDIAGONAL
covariance (nearest-neighbor interaction), requiring only 3 states.
